examples.en: The police have new evidence which lends weight to their theory.
He lends himself to illusory hopes.
The current system lends itself to great abuse.
Her presence lends a certain cachet to the company.
The new evidence lends credibility to their theory.
This topic lends itself admirably to class discussion.
His dispassionate manner lends great force to his criticisms.
None of her books really lends itself to being made into a film.
We have new evidence that lends colour to the accusation of fraud.
Her use of old-fashioned language lends an air of formality to her writing.
